{"source": "enwiki", "kind": "wikipedia_lead", "title": "Nikollë Perkaj", "pageid": 82150511, "rev_id": 1333751556, "timestamp": "2026-01-19T15:24:01Z", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nikoll%C3%AB_Perkaj", "text": "Nikollë Perkaj (died 21 September 2025) was a Kosovar politician and chairman of the Albanian Democratic National Front , who ran as a candidate for mayor of Gjakova in the 2025 local elections . He died during the election campaign , leading several political parties to suspend campaign activities in Gjakova in his honor.", "images": [{"file_title": "File:Question book-new.svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/99/Question_book-new.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 512, "height": 399, "size_bytes": 13175}, {"file_title": "File:Wiki letter w.svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 44, "height": 44, "size_bytes": 7076}]}
{"source": "enwiki", "kind": "wikipedia_lead", "title": "Peter Suder", "pageid": 82147276, "rev_id": 1333751569, "timestamp": "2026-01-19T15:24:06Z", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Suder", "text": "Peter Jovan Suder (born July 29, 2003) [ citation needed ] is an American college basketball player for the Miami RedHawks of the Mid-American Conference (MAC). He previously played for the Bellarmine Knights .\n\nHe earned 2023 ASUN All-Freshman honors. He was the leading scorer and a 2025 first team All-MAC honoree for the first 25-win Miami Redhawks basketball team (2024–25) and the Pre-Season MAC Player of the year for the record-setting 2025–26 Miami RedHawks men's basketball team .\n\nIn high school he was a starter on Carmel High School 's 2019 and 2021 Indiana High School Athletic Association (IHSAA) state champion basketball teams as a freshman and junior. He is the son of basketball player Rick Suder and the great-grandson of baseball player Pete Suder .", "images": [{"file_title": "File:Peter Suder (cropped).jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a2/Peter_Suder_%28cropped%29.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 1174, "height": 1765, "size_bytes": 877040}]}
