{"source": "enwiki", "kind": "wikipedia_lead", "title": "Nanshe Catena", "pageid": 82145833, "rev_id": 1333751586, "timestamp": "2026-01-19T15:24:12Z", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nanshe_Catena", "text": "Nanshe Catena is a crater chain on Ganymede , the largest moon of planet Jupiter. The crater chain is 103.8 kilometres (64.5 mi) long and about 50 kilometres (31 mi) wide, and it is composed of around seven individual ray craters that are closely overlapping each other, forming a line or chain.", "images": [{"file_title": "File:Crab Nebula.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/00/Crab_Nebula.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 3864, "height": 3864, "size_bytes": 14508851}, {"file_title": "File:Earth-moon.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5c/Earth-moon.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 3000, "height": 2400, "size_bytes": 995863}, {"file_title": "File:Ganymede - Perijove 34 Composite.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/21/Ganymede_-_Perijove_34_Composite.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 3445, "height": 3445, "size_bytes": 38110920}, {"file_title": "File:Nanshe Catena Galileo a.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f4/Nanshe_Catena_Galileo_a.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 540, "height": 540, "size_bytes": 296805}, {"file_title": "File:Nanshe Catena Juno.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/67/Nanshe_Catena_Juno.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 960, "height": 828, "size_bytes": 93436}, {"file_title": "File:Nanshe Catena.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/14/Nanshe_Catena.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 441, "height": 354, "size_bytes": 111944}, {"file_title": "File:Solar system.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/83/Solar_system.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 4500, "height": 5600, "size_bytes": 4225968}]}
{"source": "enwiki", "kind": "wikipedia_lead", "title": "Edward Neufville Crosse", "pageid": 81711658, "rev_id": 1333751593, "timestamp": "2026-01-19T15:24:14Z", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Neufville_Crosse", "text": "Brigadier Edward Neufville Crosse , CBE , MC and Bar (19 January 1898 – 9 October 1970), was an officer in the British Army who served during the First World War , the Iraqi Revolt , and the Second World War .\n\nCrosse served as a junior officer with the Royal Field Artillery on the Western Front during the First World War, and was mentioned in despatches and awarded the Military Cross . Crosse fought in the Battle of the Somme , during which two of his four brothers were killed and another wounded. He continued to serve in the interwar period and was awarded a Bar to his Military Cross for conspicuous gallantry in Iraq in 1920.\n\nDuring the Second World War he held staff positions in the War Office until 1943, when he became commander of the 100th Anti-Aircraft Brigade . He led the brigade through the campaign in North West Europe , for which he was appointed Commander of the Order of the British Empire (CBE) in 1945. In March 1945, he became Commander, Royal Artillery, of the 49th (West Riding) Infantry Division for their final push to liberate the Netherlands, and after the surrender of German forces there he was tasked with overseeing the disarmament and internment of the 34th SS Volunteer Grenadier Division . For this service he was made a Knight Commander of the Order of Orange-Nassau (with Swords) .\n\nIn June 1945 he was appointed Commander, Corps Royal Artillery, I Corps as part of the British Army of the Rhine , where he remained until March 1948. In November of that year he took his final posting as aide-de-camp to King George VI , a post he held until his retirement in May 1951.", "images": [{"file_title": "File:Edward Neufville Cross 1931.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/ea/Edward_Neufville_Cross_1931.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 2244, "height": 2326, "size_bytes": 7488941}, {"file_title": "File:Flag of the British Army.svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/27/Flag_of_the_British_Army.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 710, "height": 406, "size_bytes": 84708}, {"file_title": "File:Flag of the United Kingdom.svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/ae/Flag_of_the_United_Kingdom.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 1200, "height": 600, "size_bytes": 672}, {"file_title": "File:Iraq's 1920 Revolution.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/cc/Iraq%27s_1920_Revolution.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 1200, "height": 1150, "size_bytes": 356851}, {"file_title": "File:Map of the Battle of the Somme, 1916.svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/ab/Map_of_the_Battle_of_the_Somme%2C_1916.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 1204, "height": 921, "size_bytes": 541407}, {"file_title": "File:The British Army in North-west Europe 1944-45 B10435.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/bc/The_British_Army_in_North-west_Europe_1944-45_B10435.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 1297, "height": 1300, "size_bytes": 369808}]}
