{"source": "enwiki", "kind": "wikipedia_lead", "title": "Ries impact", "pageid": 81690421, "rev_id": 1333751697, "timestamp": "2026-01-19T15:24:51Z", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ries_impact", "text": "The Ries impact (also known as the Ries event ) was an asteroid impact that occurred approximately 15 million years ago in what is now southern Germany . The resulting impact crater , the Nördlinger Ries , has a diameter of about 24 km (15 mi), indicating the release of an enormous amount of energy. The nearby Steinheim Basin and a number of smaller craters on the Franconian Jura and in the Lake Constance area are, according to more recent findings, not contemporaneous with the Nördlinger Ries and are therefore not part of the Ries event.", "images": [{"file_title": "File:Merge-arrow.svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/aa/Merge-arrow.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 50, "height": 20, "size_bytes": 2619}, {"file_title": "File:Nördlinger Ries Relief Map, SRTM-1.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/N%C3%B6rdlinger_Ries_Relief_Map%2C_SRTM-1.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 1600, "height": 1200, "size_bytes": 1456431}, {"file_title": "File:Ries Impact 1 de.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Ries_Impact_1_de.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 769, "height": 153, "size_bytes": 6182}, {"file_title": "File:Ries Impact 2.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f5/Ries_Impact_2.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 769, "height": 145, "size_bytes": 6144}, {"file_title": "File:Ries Impact 3.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/cf/Ries_Impact_3.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 769, "height": 310, "size_bytes": 27617}, {"file_title": "File:Ries Impact 4.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e4/Ries_Impact_4.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 769, "height": 309, "size_bytes": 32578}, {"file_title": "File:Ries Impact 5 de.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/82/Ries_Impact_5_de.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 769, "height": 295, "size_bytes": 15905}, {"file_title": "File:Ries Profile de.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/ca/Ries_Profile_de.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 769, "height": 295, "size_bytes": 16337}, {"file_title": "File:Ries Steinheim SW.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a1/Ries_Steinheim_SW.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 1024, "height": 768, "size_bytes": 247308}, {"file_title": "File:RiesSteinheimMarkings.JPG", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/02/RiesSteinheimMarkings.JPG", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 1280, "height": 948, "size_bytes": 400278}, {"file_title": "File:Storax Sedan nuke.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7d/Storax_Sedan_nuke.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "width": 1476, "height": 1168, "size_bytes": 190791}]}
{"source": "enwiki", "kind": "wikipedia_lead", "title": "2026 Asian Men's Handball Championship", "pageid": 81693904, "rev_id": 1333751705, "timestamp": "2026-01-19T15:24:53Z", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_Asian_Men%27s_Handball_Championship", "text": "The 2026 Asian Men's Handball Championship was the 22nd edition of the Asian Men's Handball Championship , the biennial international men's handball championship of Asia and Oceania organized by AHF . The tournament was held from 15 to 29 January 2026 in Sabah Al-Salem , Kuwait.\n\nIt was the fourth time in history that the championship was organised by the Kuwait Handball Association .\n\nIt also acted as a qualification tournament for the 2027 World Men's Handball Championship in Germany , with top four teams from the championship directly qualifying for the event. If Australia would have finished inside the top five, they would have qualified as well, as the representative of Oceania.\n\nQatar were the six time defending champions, recently beating Japan 30–24 in the 2024 final in Isa Town . Bahrain won their first title with a win over Qatar in the final.", "images": [{"file_title": "File:2026 Asian Men's Handball Championship.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/3b/2026_Asian_Men%27s_Handball_Championship.png", "mime": "image/png", "width": 316, "height": 316, "size_bytes": 69205}, {"file_title": "File:Asia (orthographic projection).svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/80/Asia_%28orthographic_projection%29.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 541, "height": 541, "size_bytes": 570850}, {"file_title": "File:Blank.svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9e/Blank.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 640, "height": 120, "size_bytes": 128}, {"file_title": "File:Flag of Australia (converted).svg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/88/Flag_of_Australia_%28converted%29.svg", "mime": "image/svg+xml", "width": 12